[2]
Date: 14 Jul 2000 17:35:14 -0400
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: Xinhua News Agency, story filed 14 Jul 2000 2:37 PM EST [edited]

More Russians Killed in Mushroom Poisoning
--------------------------------------------
MOSCOW (July 14) XINHUA - Toxic mushrooms have killed 6 people in the
Volgograd region in southern Russia, 4 of whom were under 14 years of age,
the Itar-Tass news agency reported Friday. The deaths came after earlier
reports that 15 people died of the same cause in the western Voronezh
region. 52 people remain hospitalized in the Volgograd region, Tass said.
In Voronezh, where 162 people fell victim to the toxic fungus, mushroom
sales have been banned.
